---
permalink: /index.html
---
<div class="[ container stack-lg ][][]">
	<header class="[ stack ][][ header ]">
		<div class="[ stack-sm ][ inset ][]">
			<p class="[][][ header__category ]">A bookmarklet</p>
			<h1 class="[][][ header__title ]">{{ metadata.site.title }}</h1>
			<p class="[][][ header__heading ]">Check your progress in the <span class="[][ nowrap ][]">New York Times</span> <a href="https://nytimes.com/puzzles/spelling-bee" class="[][ nowrap ][]">Spelling Bee</a> without leaving the puzzle.</p>
		</div>

		<figure class="[ stack-sm ][][]">
			<picture>
				<source
					srcset="/images/desktop@2x.avif"
					media="(orientation:landscape)"
					type="image/avif"
				/>
				<source
					srcset="/images/desktop@2x.jpg"
					media="(orientation:landscape)"
					type="image/jpeg"
				/>
				<source
					srcset="/images/desktop@2x.webp"
					media="(orientation:landscape)"
					type="image/webp"
				/>

				<source
					srcset="/images/mobile@2x.avif"
					media="(orientation:portrait)"
					type="image/avif"
				/>
				<source
					srcset="/images/mobile@2x.webp"
					media="(orientation:portrait)"
					type="image/webp"
				/>
				<source
					srcset="/images/mobile@2x.jpg"
					media="(orientation:portrait)"
					type="image/jpeg"
				/>

				<img
					alt="Spelling Bee puzzle with Spell Check visible."
					src="/images/desktop@2x.jpg"
				/>
			</picture>

			<figcaption
				class="[][ font-sans font-sm inset ][ header__caption ]"
			>{{ metadata.site.title }} showing the grid for a nearly completed puzzle.</figcaption>
		</figure>
	</header>

	<aside class="[ stack-xs ][][ reminder ]">
		<h2 class="[][][ reminder__heading ]">Please Note</h2>
		<p><span class="[][ nowrap ][]">{{ metadata.site.title }}</span> is made and maintained by <a href="https://ashur.cab/rera">Ashur Cabrera</a>, and is not affiliated with or endorsed by the <span class="[][ nowrap ][]">New York Times</span>.</p>
	</aside>

	<main class="[ stack-lg ][][]">
		<section
			class="[ stack-sm ][ inset ][ section ]"
			id="usage"
		>
			<h2 class="[][][ section__heading ]">How it works</h2>
			<p>After <a href="#install">installing</a> the {{ metadata.site.title }} bookmarklet, open the <a href="https://nytimes.com/puzzles/spelling-bee">Spelling Bee</a> in your web browser.</p>
			<p>Whenever you need a nudge in the right direction or just want to check your progress, click or tap the bookmarklet: the {{ metadata.site.title }} window will appear right over your puzzle.</p>
			<p>Click or tap the <strong aria-label="close button">×</strong> in the upper right to dismiss the window and continue playing.</p>

			<h3 class="[][][ section__subheading ]">What does the grid tell me?</h3>
			<p>Sourced from the daily grid at the <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/spotlight/spelling-bee-forum">Spelling Bee Forum</a>, {{ metadata.site.title }} shows the number of words remaining for each letter.</p>
			<p>For example, a <strong>2</strong> in the <strong>7</strong> column of row <strong>G</strong> means two more 7-letter words that start with “G” are left.</p>
			<picture>
				<source
					srcset="/images/grid-highlight@2x.avif"
					type="image/avif"
				/>
				<source
					srcset="/images/grid-highlight@2x.webp"
					type="image/webp"
				/>
				<img
					alt="Spell Check grid showing two remaining 7-letter words that begin with G."
					height="780"
					src="/images/grid-highlight@2x.jpg"
					width="651"
				/>
			</picture>
			<p class="[][][ usage__check ]">When you’ve found every accepted solution for a given letter and length, a green checkmark lets you know there are no words left to uncover</p>
		</section>

		<section
			class="[ stack-sm ][ inset ][ section ]"
			id="install"
		>
			<header class="[ stack-xs ][][]">
				<h2 class="[][][ section__heading ]">Installation</h2>
				<p>{{ metadata.site.title }} is supported by most modern web browsers, including those listed below.</p>
			</header>

			<div class="[ stack-xs ][][ install__categories ]">
				<article class="[][][ install__category ]">
					<h3 class="[][][ install__heading ]">
						<button class="install__button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="install-android">
							Android (Chrome)
						</button>
					</h3>
					<div id="install-android" class="install__content" hidden="">

					</div>
				</article>

				<article class="[][][ install__category ]">
					<h3 class="[][][ install__heading ]">
						<button class="install__button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="install-ios">
							iOS (Safari)
						</button>
					</h3>
					<div id="install-ios" class="install__content" hidden="">

					</div>
				</article>

				<article class="[][][ install__category ]">
					<h3 class="[][][ install__heading ]">
						<button class="install__button" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="install-desktop">
							Desktop (Chrome, Firefox, Safari)
						</button>
					</h3>
					<div id="install-desktop" class="install__content">
						<ol class="[ stack-xs ][][ install__steps ]">
							<li>Open your browser’s bookmarks toolbar</li>
							<li>Click and drag this <a class="[][][ install__bookmarklet ]" href="#">{{ metadata.site.title }}</a> bookmarklet to the toolbar</li>
						</ol>
					</div>
				</article>
		</section>
	</main>

	<footer class="[ stack-sm ][][ footer ]">
		<h2 class="[][][ footer__heading ]">{{ metadata.site.title }}</h2>
		<ul class="[ stack-sm ][][ footer__links ]">
			<li><a class="[][ no-underline ][]" href="https://github.com/ashur/spellcheck">View source</a></li>
			<li><a class="[][ no-underline ][]" href="https://twitter.com/ashur">Report an issue</a></li>
		</ul>
	</footer>
</div>

<script>

</script>
